      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a pretty strong take. But what about people who are struggling right now? If the government focuses on debt instead of things like healthcare or food assistance, isn't that basically saying the math matters more than people's actual lives? How do you justify ignoring those immediate needs?",
